rComments: Professor Khan is very nice and really knows how to teach. Her teaching is always clear and she makes sure the class understands the concepts before moving on. She's also really funny and you'll really enjoy going to her lectures. Her tests are fair and you'll do well if you study the material.
Awesome professor. Straightforward tests and she explains very well.

Amazing professor! Love the way she teaches and makes everything so clear. If you pay attention and do your readings you'll do amazing in the course! And I Also Think She's Hot. Very nice and approachable :)
Amazing professor! Love the way she teaches and makes everything so clear. If you pay attention and do your readings you'll do amazing in the course! Very nice and approachable :)

Like many people have already said, she is very approachable and really cares about her students. I've been lucky to have her for three courses throughout my undergrad-abnormal psych (PSY240),Hormones and Behaviour(PSY395) and a seminar course in 4th year. Attendance is mandatory, but her classes are very fun, so why would you even want to skip? :p

AMAZING professor. Never felt so engaged into the lectures beside Dax, however she is so sweet and always willing to help.she really explains concepts in GREAT detail and helps you understand the material in lectures.
She's no Dax, but still a good prof. Explains things well. Tests are super easy.
She's awesome, went to her office hours, really approachable nd she's the reason I'm planning to major in psych

Okay, I have no background in science.  I went to her office hours to ask for help and asked her questions during class.  In the end, I did great in the course.  Advice for non-science people, take the time to ask questions and get help and don't be scared to take this course.

VERY HELPFUL!  Attending class is a must.  Gives lots of tips on how to do well on tests. Explains complicated slides multiple times so you walk out knowing the material. This is one of those courses where people who try their best to understand the concepts get the mark that they deserve.
Her tests are all biology based, it is extremely difficult for a student with no science background to do well in this course.
Amazing Lecturer!! Great proffesor.. If you read the textbook and understood her lectures you will be fine!!
Only had one lecture with Dr. Khan, she seems very good. I guess we will see once tests start coming.

She explains the concepts very well. You can get an A if you study well, attend all lectures, highlight the important stuff that she says in class and do the sample test that she posts before the tests and exams.

I just wanna say that for the midterm I did all the readings prior to class, attended all lectures and took great detailed notes, studies both notes and the text simultaneously like she suggested and did studied my A off in general for several hours a day. And I got a 68 !! The m/c questions were extremely unreasonable and focused on minor details
excellent prof. work hard and you'll get the grade. she's fair, understanding, and patient.

Although, she wants to help and tries to help her students, the amount of material covered is insane. You have to know her lectures down, study several biological processes discussed in class and read the text. One may take three courses in place of this course. It is very heavy so prepare early. However, psych courses at utm are heavy in general.
amazing prof.. attending lecs is mandatory if you want to get an A and doing all the necessary readings are mandatory as well. Tests are hard but if you study the lecs thoroughly you will do good!

Amazing class. She presented the normally-taboo material with a great deal of maturity. This class is good because it's not just senseless memorization of facts that have no real-world application... this class is very informative about sex and is very practical. If you're interested in this kind of thing, I'd highly recommend taking it with her.

She is a great lecturer, and that's why her lectures are mandatory and VERY helpful if you pay attention & do your best instead of wishing for an A. Her tests are tough but when I finished my test, I always felt that I could've done better because I didn't study hard. If you work hard, A is a possibility.

Great Prof! Available to answer questions & goes out of her way to make sure students understand course concepts.  Like other people said in the reviews below, tests are fair if you study.  I'm surprised at some of the comments since it is TOTALLY possible to get an A in her course.  If you study the text and attend lectures, an A is a done deal!
After taking her course I dropped out of the psychology major. I couldn't handle psychology in general. Psychology is hard.
Dr. Khan's tests are fair only if you study.  The formula for a high grade is simple, make sure you go to class, pay attention to what she says and study from day 1.  A high grade is guaranteed!

Coherent with her instructions. The course structure allows you to enter into the finals with good grades (entered with 81%)... The final will not be easy: I was told so before hand and worked hard for it. Still ended with a 71% in the course after finals.

I think people are being too tough on her.  She expects you to work hard and if you attend class and actually pay attention and read the textbook, it is possible to get an A in her course! Ooh and she gives a lot of hints for tests.  She even gave us a huge hint on an essay question that showed up on the final exam.

If you read this Dr. Khan, can you please stop making your tests so hard? why do you make them so hard? the course should be made so that those who put in the work do well, but many ppl i talked to said if they study a little they get 60-70 and those who say they study a lot get a 70-75 or something. whyyyy?? i wanna take ur class but im scared.

No doubt, she's a brilliant woman and very good lecturer... amazing at explaining concepts, crystal clear, etc... Her tests are awful, however. MC is easy, T/F is mediocre, and SA/LA is deadly. It is VERY difficult to get an A in any of her classes (240, 354, 362, 395...) because tests are weighted WAY more heavily than assignments.

HARD COURSE!! test and final exam were both very difficult. many ppl dropped out. A is  not possible. I seriously wonder whether more than 1 person got an A in course. I doubt it. too many assignments, all graded very hard. on test highest mark was so low and she acted like it was so high and she said the class did well, when we did not do well.

difficult course. TA and prof both picky markers. lose marks for nonsense. B possible but A+ not possible. bet very few lucky to get A- therefore dropped class after much thought. work i put into this class affected all other classes. too much work, very difficult to be successful in class. my girlfriend said it is hard class too,she very smart :(

this is a class where all the slackers get their C or B- and the hard workers struggle for an A. i dropped cause an A isn't even possible and I am an A and A+ student.She told us the highest mark on the test was 87!That is very low for the highest mark! The average is a 70 cause the dummies get their C, no one fails and no one gets A+, 1 gets an A

Great professor. Attend all lectures - she simplifies and clarifies concepts. Make sure to do the readings too. Flashcards really helped me in this course because there is just so much to memorize. Get the past tests/exams. She repeats and slightly changes questions. 80%+ doable with effort and hard work!
GPA buster. I don't recommend taking her course. She is very rude and his not helpful. Hard grader. If you are not sure what psychology course to take don't take this course thinking it will be easy.

Professor Khan is THE BEST psychology professor at UTM hands down! She is an amazing lecturer and really wants her students to do well. Tests are fair, but you must study. Textbook is a mandatory read. The best quality about her is she comes across as a genuine, real person that you can talk to and ask questions. Plus she has a great sense of humor

I've had her 3 times. My favourite professor I've ever had. No contest. To the individuals who are criticizing her of her hard marking, perhaps didn't study hard enough. Listen in class, read the textbook, study well and you'll easily get an A. Tests are fair & marked fair. Studying is a breeze since she drills the info hard during lectures anyways

Probably the best Psych prof I've had since Dr. Dax.  She's like a running train.  Once she starts a lecture, she doesn't stop-it's all business.  You best bring your note-taking game.  Very clear and knowledgeable of material!  Fair tests.  Informative slides.  I love the textbook.  No complaints.

Really easy and clear professor. I've had her for PSY295 and 354, she sticks with the textbook and does not introduce other information. Books are not very difficult to understand. Her tests are average in difficulty. 295 has an in-class assignment which is pretty simple. Exam was a bit harder than expected but still got an A.

not amazing, shes really clear when she speaks but ridiculous marker! sOOOO hard to get a decent mark... people who like her only like her because they did well.. I've had her twice and both times so difficult to get a decent mark doing the readings and attending every lecture only managed to get me a 56!
Wonderful Prof :)

Very good professor. She is interesting in the lectures. And very easy to talk to. Read the textbook. Tests multiple choice, true/false, essay questions. Reasonable time to do the tests. Assignments were small but she wants to get you thinking.
PSY295 AMAZING PROFESSOR! SHE WAS VERY ENERGETIC, DOESNT BORE YOU, MAKES THE MATERIAL REALLY INTERESTING TO LISTEN TO. OVERALL ONE OF THE BEST PROFs!

Amazing course and amazing prof. Her tests were very straight-forward. Only thing I didn't quite like is she'd turn all the lights on during lecture but then off for a video then all back on, then off again for another video. Aside from having the lights on @ max, she's an amazing prof. Responds to emails right away.

I had her for PSY295 (Neuro). One of the best profs in psych. She doesn't demand too much and is more focussed on the students understanding the general concepts. Tests are fair. Just attend lectures for details and keep up on the readings and you'll do fine. Highly recommend her

Wonderful! Absolutely wonderful. This is one of the BEST profs at UTM. Go to class, that is very important. Read the text book. You will need to know lectures and text thoroughly for tests, but her lectures are amazing and she is reasonable & helpful
I Love her!!! She is a very nice prof. It's pretty simple to me... go to class and read the book and study... and you'll pass!!! I would definitely take one of her classes again.

shes a really good prof!...really likes to help students with anything...very fast response to emails ..however tests are somewhat difficult because she takes minute details from the textbook..but recommended prof for sure
Helpful and a good class, though she doesn't always state her expectations clearly. I highly recommend her anyway.
found her lectures very interesting. approachable prof. she tries to make her lecture applicable and interesting enough for students.
